Algidus i, m. : a range of fertile hills between Praeneste and the Mons Albanus, SE. of Rome. It was famous for the excellence of its pasturage and the fine growth of its oak woods (IV. iv. 58). Its height rendered it cold (nivalis, III. xxiii. 9).
